The paper focuses on explaining the decision-making process of deep reinforcement learning agents in Atari games through visual attentional patterns. This involves generating saliency maps and analyzing how agents evolve during the learning phase. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.CV (computer vision), and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper also tests its method on non-expert human subjects, indicating a potential focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of deep RL suggests a possible connection to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
